  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc8 \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0b85\u0baa\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f  \u0bae\u0bc2\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd  \u0b95\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Three arrested for trying to hijack Navy soldier's gun",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "Ja-Ela police have arrested three people, including a man who tried to snatch a gun from a naval soldier who was on security duty at a petrol station in the Ekala area in Ja-Ela.",
        "During the incident on the 22nd, one of the suspects tried to snatch the gun of a Marine who was on security duty at the petrol station.",
        "Police said the incident was clearly recorded on a CCTV camera fitted at the petrol station.",
        "Ja-Ela Police Station Officer-in-Charge R. M. G. D. Ratnayake led by Inspector Sampath Dissanayake in charge of the Complaints Division, Police Sergeant (35599) Vanninayake and Police Constable (24346) Silva are conducting further investigations."
      ],
